"Oh, are we turning this into a bad sci-fi movie from the '80s now?" Albino remarked, his voice laced with a hint of sarcasm as he pushed himself upright. Despite the odds stacked against him, there was a glimmer of amusement in his eyes, a testament to his unshakeable resolve in the face of danger.

As he squared off against the android, Albino knew that this would be not as easy as everything had been up ‘till then. Although his status as a Heruka turned him into what was essentially the perfect lifeform, constantly adapting in strength, agility, durability and dexterity to improve his physical prowess or to erase his weakness when confronted against sturdy foes, his adaptive abilities were admittedly limited against robots, for they somewhat relied on flesh-to-flesh contact. They’d still work in this situation, eventually, but their pace would be slower.
